

TRACTATUS CONSCIENTIAE
ADDENDUM: LEVEL 0
The Meta-Structure Prior to All Interpretation
To be read before Part I of the main Tractatus

Why This Layer Exists
The Tractatus Conscientiae (v0.1) begins with Axiom A1: consciousness is the sole ontological primitive. This is a commitment about what occupies the role of the enabling condition. It is coherent, consistent, and supported by evidence nodes. But it is one filling of a structural role whose necessity can be established on purely formal grounds, prior to any ontological commitment.
This addendum establishes that prior layer. It asks not what reality is made of, but what must obtain for anything to appear at all. The answer is structural and minimal. From it, the Tractatus emerges as one valid derivation among several. This does not weaken the Tractatus — it grounds it more deeply.
The main Tractatus propositions (1–9) are now properly understood as theorems within Branch 4 (Nondual Metaphysics) of the interpretation layer, derived by specifying what occupies S. They remain fully valid. The spine gains a deeper root.


LEVEL 0 — THE META-STRUCTURE
Six propositions. Ontologically neutral. Formally necessary. These concern the conditions under which any content — physical, mental, mathematical, or otherwise — can appear at all.

L0.1   For anything to appear, three structural moments must obtain simultaneously.
L0.1.1   S — an enabling condition that constitutes the possibility of distinction.
L0.1.2   0 — a pole of observation / subjectivity.
L0.1.3   1 — a pole of the observed / objectivity.
L0.1.4   These three are mutually constitutive. No one of them can obtain without the other two.

Formal statement:   S ⇒ (0 ↔ 1)
S enables 0 and 1 as mutually dependent poles.
Neither 0 nor 1 is self-grounding. Both depend on S.

L0.2   S is the enabling condition. This framework makes no claim about what S is.
L0.2.1   S is not specified as consciousness, matter, mathematics, process, or any other substance.
L0.2.2   The formal requirement is only that something play the role of enabling condition.
L0.2.3   Any ontology, to be coherent, must identify what occupies S. The identification is the ontology.

L0.3   0 and 1 are mutually dependent and neither is self-grounding.
L0.3.1   0 cannot be the source of 1, nor 1 the source of 0. Both are enabled by S.
L0.3.2   Observer and observed co-arise. There is no observer without something observed; no observed without something observing.
L0.3.3   This is the formal structure of dependent origination (pratītyasamutpāda), stated without Buddhist metaphysical commitment.

L0.4   A structural error is possible: 0 can misidentify itself as S.
L0.4.1   This error has the form: Sv(0) — the observer claims self-grounding status.
L0.4.2   The error is not epistemic (a false belief about content). It is structural: a misidentification of one’s position in the enabling relation.
L0.4.3   Under Sv(0), 0 treats itself as the source of both 0 and 1. It exempts itself from the dependence it observes in everything else.
L0.4.4   This is the formal structure of what traditions call ego, avidya (ignorance), ahamkara (I-making), or the illusion of independent selfhood.

L0.5   Recognition is the cessation of the Sv(0) error.
L0.5.1   Recognition has the form: ¬Sv(0) — the observer sees its own dependence on S.
L0.5.2   Recognition is not acquisition of new content. The structural relation was always obtaining. Recognition is the cessation of a misidentification.
L0.5.3   Recognition is structurally identical across all interpretations of S. Whether S is consciousness, physics, mathematics, or process, the Sv(0) error has the same form and its cessation has the same form.
L0.5.4   This is why contemplative traditions with incompatible metaphysics (Madhyamaka, Advaita Vedanta, Zen, Christian mysticism) converge on similar phenomenological accounts of liberation. The practice operates at Level 0, below the interpretation layer.

L0.6   Level 0 is itself a conceptual construction. It does not survive recognition.
L0.6.1   The three-term structure S ⇒ (0 ↔ 1) is a thought arising for an observer. It is itself subject to L0.3.
L0.6.2   The framework is a pointer. Like all pointers, it ceases to be needed when recognition is complete.
L0.6.3   This is Nagarjuna’s final move: emptiness is itself empty. The meta-structure is empty of inherent existence.
L0.6.4   What remains when even Level 0 dissolves cannot be stated within Level 0. This is not a failure of the framework. It is the framework pointing accurately at its own limit.

“Whereof one cannot speak, thereof one must be silent. — Wittgenstein, Tractatus 7”
“The raft is abandoned when the other shore is reached. — Diamond Sutra”


How the Tractatus Conscientiae Derives from Level 0
The propositions of the main Tractatus (v0.1) are valid theorems within Branch 4 (Nondual Metaphysics). They derive from Level 0 by the following steps:

Step 1  L0.1 obtains: S ⇒ (0 ↔ 1)
Step 2  Phenomenological observation: 0 is immediately given as awareness.
        Physical exteriority (1) is inferred, not immediately given.
Step 3  Hypothesis: S is best understood as pure awareness — the ground
        from which both 0 and 1 arise as contractions / modulations.
Step 4  Derive A1 (Tractatus v0.1 Axiom 1):
        Consciousness is the sole ontological primitive.
Step 5  All subsequent Tractatus propositions (1–9) follow within this branch.

This derivation is valid. It is not the only valid derivation. Steps 2–3 make specific phenomenological and metaphysical commitments. Different commitments at those steps produce different branches.


The Six Interpretation Branches
Each branch fills S with a specific occupant. All six preserve the L0 structure. All six permit the Sv(0) error and its cessation. They differ only in what they identify as the enabling condition.

B1  Thin Formalism   S = the minimal formal condition itself
S is the structure S ⇒ (0 ↔ 1) with no positive ontological content. The framework as empty scaffolding. No claims about what grounds the scaffolding. Closest to Madhyamaka: the enabling condition is itself empty of inherent existence. Recognition = seeing that even S is dependently arisen.
B2  Physical Realism   S = the nomological structure of physical reality
S = state-space + dynamical laws. 0 and 1 are physical systems. Consciousness is an emergent feature of sufficiently complex physical configurations. This is the mainstream scientific ontology. Compatible with L0 provided physics can account for the observer. Problem: the hard problem persists — why does physical structure produce phenomenal experience at all?
B3  Platonic / Computational Realism   S = mathematical pattern space / the Ruliad
S = the space of all possible mathematical/computational forms (Levin’s Platonic space; Wolfram’s Ruliad). 0 and 1 are specific computational processes sampling threads through S. The laws of physics follow from the constraints of any bounded observer embedded in S. Recognition = an observer recognising its own position within the computational structure. Langan’s CTMU is a formal elaboration of this branch.
B4  Nondual Metaphysics   S = pure consciousness / awareness
S = self-luminous awareness (Paramashiva; Brahman; ground luminosity). 0 = localised contraction of S. 1 = extrinsic appearance of other contractions. The main Tractatus Conscientiae (v0.1, Propositions 1–9) is the full development of this branch. Recognition = contraction recognising itself as S (¬Sv(0) = pratyabhijna).
B5  Process Metaphysics   S = ongoing relational becoming
S = the continuous emergence of distinction (Whitehead’s process; Rovelli’s relational events). There is no static substrate. Reality is pure relational flux. 0 and 1 are momentary occasions of experience arising in relation. Recognition = an occasion of experience recognising itself as process rather than substance. Compatible with Rovelli’s relational QM and the Madhyamaka process reading.
B6  Cross-Life Continuity   S = a mechanism enabling trans-instantiation pattern persistence
S = whatever enables the karmic update rule: I_(n+1) = Ψ(P, K_n, ε). This branch remains agnostic about what S ultimately is; it only requires that something play the role of maintaining pattern identity across instantiations. Compatible with Branches 3, 4, and 5. The bardo cartography and tukdam data bear directly on this branch regardless of which primary ontology is correct.



